modules.description: Provides compression and decompression of byte sequences using the Snappy algorithm. Operates on raw byte arrays and strings, ensuring fast processing for data serialization tasks. Used to reduce storage size and improve I/O performance in networked applications.

Provides functions to compress and decompress strings using Snappy algorithm, with variants that operate on subranges of input buffers. Works with raw string data and includes methods to validate, size, and manipulate compressed content. Used for efficient data transmission and storage, such as compressing log entries or serializing binary data.
